ing configuration and the client will operate normally but we will not have any way of distinguishing work units you completed from the work units others with the same name have completed and you will not be eligible for the new bonus points program currently available in the smp2 client why does the passkey web page ask for my email address we send the passkey to you by email if we just displayed the passkey on the web page then anybody could claim a passkey in your name sending the passkey to your email account is more secure because only you have access to your email account note we recommend using an email address that you plan to keep for an extended period of time if you ever lose your passkey you can get another copy of the same passkey by submitting another request using the same fah user name and same email address is there an easy way to enter the passkey into the client yes in the console client setup there is a new passkey prompt passkey you can copy your passkey from the email you receive from fah and paste it in to that prompt on windows to paste into the console prompt right click on the title bar then select paste from the menu that appears it is strongly recommended that the client cfg file not be manually edited as it's not a plain text file and could become corrupted in the windows gui client paste your passkey in to the passkey field at the bottom of the user tab in the client configuration window on a macintosh console client command c to copy and command v to paste in the v7 setup the windows v7 installer has a prompt to enter a passkey after a name and or team number in the v7 fahcontrol a passkey can be added under the configure button identity tab passkey field should i keep my passkey secret in general yes do not post a passkey on the forum etc the natural exceptions to this general rule are using the passkey in the client of course as well as folding home web sites and related sites we are working to use the passkey to allow donors to get more information about their folding home client machines also we are working with partners to use the passkey to validate donor's names with their emails currently the only such example is the pny folding home contest please do use your passkey with this web site but at the moment this is the only site that we have authorized passkey use so do not use it with any other site what do i do if i forgot or lost my passkey go to the passkey web page and fill in the same information as before you will get another email with your same passkey note if your original email address is no longer accesible you will need to enter a new email address and you will be sent a new and different passkey for more information please see fah faq v6 fah client faq folding support forum last updated on may 24 2011 at 10 08 am
